[00:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'So, part one, what is Hermes? Hermes Agent is an open-source AI agent built by new research and it\'s a lab behind the Hermes model family. Most agents are built by tool companies.'

[01:05] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'This one is built by the people who trained the models and that matters. And more on that in a second. It runs in your terminal as a CLI or as a gateway that can answer on your phone via Telegram, Discord, Slack, iMessage,'

[01:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'WeChat. They have 16 platforms as of the latest version. It\'s provider agnostic, so you can use Claude, you can use GPT, Grok, Kimi, you can use a local model via Ollama,'

[01:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'or anything else. Hermes doesn\'t care, you can pick exactly what you want. So, why does this exist? New research trains models. They built Hermes originally as a the harm harness that'

[01:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'generates training data. So, when you use Hermes, you\'re using the same tool new research used to build the next generation of their models. And that\'s a credibility signal you don\'t often get. And this is obviously open-source, MIT licensed as of this'

[01:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'recording around 7,000 stars on GitHub, nearly 300 contributors and it\'s moving fast. We literally just got the the most recent version 0.9.0 today. So, the key bet of Hermes Agent is'

[02:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'compounding value. Most agents are stateless. So, every session starts from zero. Every ChatGPT session starts blank. Every new Claude conversation starts blank.'

[02:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Open Claude usually the same. Hermes was built differently. Every session feeds the next one. So, there\'s a four-step loop here. You give it a task. It could be anything. It records a trajectory. And'

[02:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'this is the tools used, every decision made, every result. And then it can extract that as a reusable skill based on how it worked. So, the next time it\'s faster, more accurate and cost less'

[02:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'tokens. And this is compounding value as a thesis and what makes Hermes really unique. A Hermes installed that you\'ve had for 3 months is fundamentally better than what you set up yesterday.'

